bridget — authorship and fork lineage
=====================================

bridget is a Pogo ↔ Discord bridge, originally written by Clover Ross and
licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later. This file records the lineage so downstream
forks-of-forks can trace authorship; the LICENSE file holds the legal text.

Original author and upstream
----------------------------

  Clover Ross  <cloverross@dreamuniversegames.com>
  https://github.com/cloverross/bridget

Copyright (C) 2026 Clover Ross.

Per-file notices
----------------

Every source file carries a copyright line, an `SPDX-License-Identifier:
GPL-3.0-or-later` tag, and the GPL's warranty disclaimer. Which names appear is
decided by the git history, not by convention:

  - Files that originated upstream and were changed here — `bridget`,
    `install.sh`, `build.sh`, `test.sh`, `tests/smoke-fresh-install.*` — carry
    both copyrights and a notice of modification with its date, as GPL-3.0
    section 5(a) requires of a modified file.
  - Files written for this fork and absent upstream — all of `bridget_core/`
    and the rest of `tests/` — carry the fork maintainer's copyright and say
    so.

To re-derive who touched what:

  git log --format='%aN' -- <path> | sort -u

Fork maintainer (this repository)
---------------------------------

  Daniel Miller  <gate46dmiller@gmail.com>
  https://github.com/drellem2/bridget

This fork layers two additive features on top of upstream:

  - P1: env-key generalizations (commit f6ef795, tag p1-fork-layer)
  - P2: per-channel agent routing (commit 08532ce, tag p2-fork-layer)

Each layer is intended to PR back to upstream once it has seen enough
operator use. See the README's "Fork status" section for the upstream
trajectory. Architectural rationale lives in
`docs/bridget-integration-design.md` in the maintainer's pogo repository
(not redistributed here — request access from the fork maintainer for
context).

Contributors
------------

Beyond the original author and the fork maintainer, contributors to either
the upstream or this fork are recorded in the git history. To list them:

  git log --format='%aN <%aE>' | sort -u

License
-------

GPL-3.0-or-later. See LICENSE. All contributions to either upstream or this
fork are accepted under the same license.
